content:
The third step in decision optimization is to configure the model’s recommendation. Recommendations are based on the model's actionable variables and appear as suggested improvements. To optimize Einstein's suggestions for improving the predicted outcome:

Select the actionable variables that you want included in the optimization results.
Optionally, click Add Constraint and select a constraint type to configure your logic.

CONSTRAINT TYPE	DESCRIPTION	EXAMPLE
Count of records	Limit recommendations based on the number of records.	“‘Give free t-shirt”' can be recommended only 100 times because only 100 t-shirts are available.
Aggregate across records	Limit recommendations based on the cumulative sum among all records.	“Offer Discount” can be recommended only if the company-wide budget for discounts isn’t exceeded.
Single record	Limit recommendations based on specific characteristics of an individual record.	“Send Field Service” can be recommended only if the site is near a service center.

Optionally, add a condition to specify which records the constraint is applied to.

After a constraint is applied, it’s listed as a constraint, and you can edit or delete it. 

You can express a record-level exclusion by using a boundary value of 0 combined with a condition.
title: Configuring Decision Optimization in Salesforce
